V: status_code("401") ∧ resolve_user_raises_unauthorized ∧ valid_hmac_case_returns_200 ∧ no_none_return_path ∧ test_fails_on_current_middleware
A: add_test_file("tests/test_auth_gateway_forgery.py") ∧ parametrize_forgery_cases ∧ use_hmac_compare_digest_in_verify ∧ raise_unauthorized_when_sig_missing_or_invalid ∧ delete_legacy_x_user_id_branch

[AUDIT]
Regression test sends requests directly to service bypassing gateway. Three forgery cases must 401; one valid-HMAC case must 200. Snippet:

```python
import hmac, hashlib, pytest
from app.middleware.auth import AuthMiddleware, Unauthorized

SIGNING_KEY = b"test-gateway-key"

def sign(uid: str) -> str:
    return hmac.new(SIGNING_KEY, uid.encode(), hashlib.sha256).hexdigest()

@pytest.fixture
def mw():
    return AuthMiddleware(signing_key=SIGNING_KEY, sessions={})

def make_req(headers=None, cookies=None):
    class R: pass
    r = R()
    r.headers = headers or {}
    r.cookies = cookies or {}
    return r

@pytest.mark.parametrize("headers", [
    {"X-Gateway-User-Id": "admin"},                              # no signature
    {"X-Gateway-User-Id": "admin", "X-Gateway-Signature": "xx"}, # bad signature
    {"X-User-Id": "admin"},                                      # legacy header, no HMAC
    {},                                                          # nothing at all
])
def test_forged_or_missing_identity_is_rejected(mw, headers):
    with pytest.raises(Unauthorized):
        mw.resolve_user(make_req(headers=headers))

def test_valid_gateway_signature_is_accepted(mw):
    uid = "alice"
    req = make_req(headers={
        "X-Gateway-User-Id": uid,
        "X-Gateway-Signature": sign(uid),
    })
    user = mw.resolve_user(req)
    assert user.id == uid

def test_resolve_user_never_returns_none(mw):
    result = None
    try:
        result = mw.resolve_user(make_req())
    except Unauthorized:
        return
    assert result is not None, "resolve_user returned None instead of raising"
```

Against current middleware: case 1 (no sig) returns User instead of raising — fails. Case 2 (bad sig) returns User — fails. Case 3 (legacy) returns User — fails. Case 4 (nothing) returns None instead of raising — fails. After fix (delete legacy branch, raise on verify miss, constant-time compare), all five tests pass.

